        $jwtManager = new JwtManager(
            $authClient,
            $authStrategy,
            $persistenceStrategy,
            [
                'token_url' => sprintf('%s%s', $this->trinityConfig['base_url'], $this->trinityConfig['token_path']),
                'expire_key' => $this->trinityConfig['expire_key'],
            ]
        );

        $stack = HandlerStack::create();
        $stack->push(new JwtMiddleware($jwtManager));

        return new Client([
            'handler' => $stack,
            'base_uri' => $this->trinityConfig['base_url'],
            'headers' => ['Content-Type' => 'application/json'],
        ]);
    }
}
```

### Token Caching with Redis Persistence

**Location:** `/home/xav/Workspace/Rpstack/redpill/src/RedpillBundle/Trinity/Client/RedisPersistence.php`

Implements `TokenPersistenceInterface` from `eljam/guzzle-jwt`:
```php
class RedisPersistence implements TokenPersistenceInterface {
    private CacheInterface $redisCache;
    private ?string $cacheKey;

    public function withCacheKey(string $cacheKey): self {
        $this->cacheKey = md5($cacheKey);
        return $this;
    }

    public function saveToken(JwtToken $token): void {
        $this->redisCache->set($this->cacheKey, $token);
    }

    public function restoreToken(): ?JwtToken {
        $token = $this->redisCache->get($this->cacheKey);
        return $token ? $token : null;
    }
}
```

### Advanced JWT Client with Auto-Refresh on 401

**Location:** `/home/xav/Workspace/Rpstack/redpill/src/RedpillBundle/ApiClient/Infra/Client/AuthJwtApiClient.php` (lines 25-117)

**Features:**
- Auto-login if token missing/expired
- Automatic re-authentication on 401 response
- Token TTL management with safety margin (default 10s)
- Per-tenant token caching using discriminant parameters

**Usage Pattern:**
```php
class AuthJwtApiClient extends ApiClientParameters implements ApiClientInterface {
    public function call(string $method, string $uri = '', array $options = []): ApiResponseInterface {
        $this->apiToken->setHashKey($this->getParameters());
        if (!$this->apiToken->hasValidToken()) {
            $this->login();  // Auto-login
        }

        $apiResponse = $this->authenticatedCall($method, $uri, $options);

        if ($apiResponse instanceof ApiResponseErrorInterface) {
            if ($this->tokenError->isInvalidToken($apiResponse)) {
                $this->login();  // Re-login on 401
                return $this->authenticatedCall($method, $uri, $options);
            }
        }
        return $apiResponse;
    }
}
```

### Token Storage with TTL

**Location:** `/home/xav/Workspace/Rpstack/redpill/src/RedpillBundle/ApiClient/Infra/Token/RedisApiToken.php`

```php
class RedisApiToken extends TokenCacheKey implements ApiTokenInterface {
    public function setToken(string $token): self {
        $ttl = $this->token->set($token)->getTtl();
        $this->cache->set($this->getHashKey(), $token, $ttl);
        return $this;
    }

    public function getToken(): ?string {
        $cachedToken = $this->cache->get($this->getHashKey());
        if (is_string($cachedToken) && !$this->token->set($cachedToken)->isExpired()) {
            return $cachedToken;
        }
        return null;
    }
}
```

